Expected Training Volatility:
There is significant volatility in the validation loss (particularly the sharp spike around epoch 12) and minor dips in accuracy.
This is the expected trade-off when using RandomHorizontalFlip, RandomRotation, and ColorJitter.
Because the model evaluates "new" variations of the images every epoch, the learning path is noisier, but the resulting model is undeniably more robust.

Initial Conclusion: The application of image augmentation directly improved the model's ability to generalize to unseen data, successfully resolving the late-stage overfitting seen in the baseline configuration.

